# --- Non-free codecs (Recommends, not Depends) -----------------------
# These pull from Debian's non-free component; live-build enables it
# so the ISO can include them via Recommends.
Recommends:
 gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad,
 gstreamer1.0-plugins-ugly,
 gstreamer1.0-libav,
 p7zip-rar,
Description: AIMS OS — desktop extras (second browser, creative, non-free codecs)
 The optional desktop layer on top of the slim aims-os-desktop. Adds
 Chromium with the French locale, full English LibreOffice support
 (help-fr, en-gb locale, English hunspell / hyphen / mythes), creative
 tools (GIMP, Inkscape, Shotwell), the Evolution mail client,
 alternative terminals and shells (fish, tilix), the flameshot
 screenshot tool, and the non-free GStreamer codecs (bad / ugly /
 libav) plus p7zip-rar for the full multimedia and archive coverage
 that v2.0 of AIMS OS shipped by default.
 .
 Install this if you want the v2.0 "everything in the ISO" experience
 without re-flashing.
